    <a href="/reading/calculus/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to calculus</a>

    <h1>Optimization</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Active Calculus &middot; CC BY-SA &middot; <a href="https://activecalculus.org">activecalculus.org</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">Find the best point. <strong>Critical points</strong> are where the gradient vanishes. The <strong>second derivative test</strong> classifies them as maxima, minima, or saddle points. <strong>Lagrange multipliers</strong> handle optimization with constraints: find the best point on a surface, not just in open space.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Critical points -->
    <h3>Critical points in several variables</h3>
    <p>A critical point of f(x, y) is where both partial derivatives are zero: grad(f) = (0, 0). These are the only candidates for local maxima and minima in the interior of the domain.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Find critical points of f(x,y) = x^2 + y^2 - 2x - 4y + 5
; grad(f) = (2x - 2, 2y - 4) = (0, 0)
; => x = 1, y = 2

(define (f x y)
  (+ (* x x) (* y y) (* -2 x) (* -4 y) 5))

(define h 0.0001)
(define (df/dx x y) (/ (- (f (+ x h) y) (f x y)) h))
(define (df/dy x y) (/ (- (f x (+ y h)) (f x y)) h))

; Check gradient at (1, 2)
(display "grad(f) at (1,2) = (")
(display (df/dx 1.0 2.0)) (display ", ")
(display (df/dy 1.0 2.0)) (display ")") (newline)
; Both near zero: critical point

(display "f(1, 2) = ") (display (f 1 2)) (newline)  ; 0 (minimum)
(display "f(0, 0) = ") (display (f 0 0)) (newline)  ; 5
(display "f(2, 4) = ") (display (f 2 4))             ; 1
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`# Critical points of f(x,y) = x^2 + y^2 - 2x - 4y + 5
def f(x, y):
    return x**2 + y**2 - 2*x - 4*y + 5

h = 1e-7
dfdx = lambda x, y: (f(x+h, y) - f(x, y)) / h
dfdy = lambda x, y: (f(x, y+h) - f(x, y)) / h

# Check gradient at (1, 2)
print("grad(f) at (1,2) = (" + format(dfdx(1.0, 2.0), ".6f") + ", " + format(dfdy(1.0, 2.0), ".6f") + ")")
print("f(1, 2) = " + str(f(1, 2)))
print("f(0, 0) = " + str(f(0, 0)))
print("f(2, 4) = " + str(f(2, 4)))
`} />
    </div>


    <!-- Second derivative test -->
    <h3>Second derivative test</h3>
    <p>At a critical point, compute the Hessian determinant D = f_xx*f_yy &minus; (f_xy)^2. If D &gt; 0 and f_xx &gt; 0, it is a local minimum. If D &gt; 0 and f_xx &lt; 0, a local maximum. If D &lt; 0, a saddle point.</p>

    <SchemeRepl client:visible initialCode={`; Second derivative test for f(x,y) = x^3 - 3xy + y^3
; Critical points: grad = (3x^2-3y, -3x+3y^2) = (0,0)
; => x^2 = y and x = y^2 => x = 0,y=0 or x=1,y=1

(define (f x y) (+ (* x x x) (* -3 x y) (* y y y)))
(define h 0.001)

(define (fxx x y)
  (/ (+ (f (+ x h) y) (f (- x h) y) (* -2 (f x y))) (* h h)))
(define (fyy x y)
  (/ (+ (f x (+ y h)) (f x (- y h)) (* -2 (f x y))) (* h h)))
(define (fxy x y)
  (/ (- (f (+ x h) (+ y h)) (f (+ x h) y)
        (f x (+ y h)) (- (f x y)))
     (* h h)))

; Test at (0, 0)
(let ((d (- (* (fxx 0.0 0.0) (fyy 0.0 0.0))
             (* (fxy 0.0 0.0) (fxy 0.0 0.0)))))
  (display "At (0,0): D = ") (display d) (newline)
  (display "  => saddle point (D < 0)") (newline))

; Test at (1, 1)
(let ((d (- (* (fxx 1.0 1.0) (fyy 1.0 1.0))
             (* (fxy 1.0 1.0) (fxy 1.0 1.0)))))
  (display "At (1,1): D = ") (display d) (newline)
  (display "  fxx = ") (display (fxx 1.0 1.0)) (newline)
  (display "  => local minimum (D > 0, fxx > 0)"))
`} />

    <div class="python-block my-2" style="display:none">
      <Repl client:visible initialCode={`import numpy as np

def f(x, y): return x**3 - 3*x*y + y**3

h = 1e-5
fxx = lambda x, y: (f(x+h,y) - 2*f(x,y) + f(x-h,y)) / h**2
fyy = lambda x, y: (f(x,y+h) - 2*f(x,y) + f(x,y-h)) / h**2
fxy = lambda x, y: (f(x+h,y+h) - f(x+h,y) - f(x,y+h) + f(x,y)) / h**2

for pt in [(0,0), (1,1)]:
    x, y = pt
    D = fxx(x,y)*fyy(x,y) - fxy(x,y)**2
    print(f"At {pt}: D={D:.2f}, fxx={fxx(x,y):.2f}")
    if D < 0: print("  => saddle point")
    elif fxx(x,y) > 0: print("  => local minimum")
    else: print("  => local maximum")
`} />
    </div>


